Introduction

Yoon Jisung is a South Korean singer under LM Entertainment. He is best known for finishing 8th in Produce 101 Season 2 and becoming a member of Wanna One until their disbandment.

In January 2019, Jisung was cast as the male lead in the musical The Days.

He made his solo debut on February 20, 2019 with his first mini album Aside.

Jisung enlisted for his military service as an active duty soldier on May 14, 2019. He was discharged early on November 20, 2020.

On April 6, 2022 Jisung signed a contract with the company DG Entertainment after terminating his contract with LM Entertainment.
